abstract: Ukraine's Pres Viktor F Yanukovich suggests that he is not bending to international pressure to free his political rival Yulia V Tymoshenko, despite desire to complete deal that would integrate country with Western Europe.
snippet: President Viktor F. Yanukovich of Ukraine suggested that he was not bending to international pressure to free Yulia V. Tymoshenko, despite a desire to integrate the country with Western Europe.
lead_paragraph: President Viktor F. Yanukovich of Ukraine suggested that he was not bending to international pressure to free Yulia V. Tymoshenko, despite a desire to integrate the country with Western Europe.

headline.main: Leader Hints Quick Release of Tymoshenko Is Unlikely
headline.print_headline: President Of Ukraine Dismisses Freeing Rival
headline.seo: Tymoshenko Won’t Be Freed Soon, Ukraine’s President Says
